cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image segmentation using deep learning techniques. The use of fully convolutional neural networks (FCNNs) and Conditional Random Fields (CRFs) also suggests that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) for CRFs training may suggest that it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the evaluation of the proposed method on imaging data provided by the Multimodal Brain Tumor Image Segmentation Challenge (BRATS) suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
